Definition B.2. Let $\mathcal{C}$ be an $\infty$-category with finite products. A model (or an algebra) in $\mathcal{C}$ for an algebraic theory $\mathbb{T}$ is a finite product preserving functor $\mathbb{T}\to\mathcal{C}$. We write $\mathrm{Mod}_{\mathbb{T}}(\mathcal{C})$ for the $\infty$-category of models of $\mathbb{T}$ in $\mathcal{C}$, i.e., for the full subcategory of $\mathrm{Fun}(\mathbb{T},\mathcal{C})$ spanned by the models.
