Definition 2.1. An $\infty$-category $\mathcal{C}$ is preadditive if it is pointed, admits finite coproducts and finite products, and the canonical morphism $C_{1}\sqcup C_{2}\to C_{1}\times C_{2}$ is an equivalence for all objects $C_{1},C_{2}\in\mathcal{C}$. In this case any such object will be denoted by $C_{1}\oplus C_{2}$ and will be referred to as a biproduct of $C_{1}$ and $C_{2}$.
